olution would be a terrible solution because the short team and the elf team would be short changed in terms of numbers, geography, and classes.<br><br>The solution is therefore to have two teams-- one team being the &quot;humanoid&quot; team or what I call the Geeks, and the other the non-humanoid team, wich I call the &quot;Freaks&quot;. This solution would allow there to be seven races on each team.<br><br>The Geeks would consist of the following:<br><br>Humans<br>Erudites<br>Barbarians<br>Wood Elves<br>High elves<br>Half elves<br>Dwarfs (Ok they are sort of humanoid; on the other hand, they are definitely Geeks)<br><br>The freaks would consist of the following:<br><br>Iskar<br>Vah Shir<br>Dark elfs<br>Ogres<br>Trolls<br>Gnomes<br>Halflings (Ok they are sort of Freaks-- I call them Asslings)<br><br>No solution is completely perfect, but this is the best solution given the constraints on the server. This would allow each team to have access to every single class, and it would allow the best break up in terms of geographic distribution, with a slight edge given to the Freaks. <br><br>The thing that makes the least sense is having the Halflings on the &quot;Freak&quot; squad, but remember that this is not Good vs. Evil. It is a race server after all, and this solution splits the teams up on loosely defined &quot;racial&quot; characteristics, and &quot;race&quot; as any thinking person knows in the twentieth century is completely arbitrarily defined.<br><br>In any case, this is the solution that I think seems the fairest-- I would implement this solution on Vallon Zek, and leave Tallon Zek as a cross-teaming server-- anyone who wants to movelog should be able to.<br><br>Chiaroc<br>almost 56 half-elf ranger <br><br>PS. Mark my word-- if they implemented this on one of the two &quot;team&quot; servers, it would undoubtedly be the more popular server, since after all, when we high level people joined this server, team play is what we were expecting.<br><br>Flame away, my friends, flame away!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uchiaroc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiaroc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/6/02 8:16:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31118.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> geeks v. freaks</span><hr size=1> Sigh... come on-- someone must be interested in commenting on my proposal.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ugildisdhorentath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gildis Dhorentath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1140<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/6/02 8:28:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31118.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: geeks v. freaks</span><hr size=1> You're talking to the wrong people. We're not Verant. <p><br><span style="width:180;position:relative;top:0;left:0">Gildis Dhorentath</span><span style="width:180;position:relative;top:0;left:0">Samaell Eternal</span><br><span style="width:180;position:relative;top:0;left:0">Iksar Necromancer</span><span>Ogre Shadowknight</span><br><span style="width:180;position:relative;top:0;left:0">Second Rising</span><span>Second Rising</span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/uaaenidl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AaeniDL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>:o</span><br>  Posts: 3332<br> <fo